title: Sydney Storm Sparks 400 SES Calls, Trees Down And Widespread Damage Across City | 10 News
description: Clean-up crews are on the ground across Sydney after a fast-moving storm unleashed giant hail, fierce winds and heavy rain overnight.  More than 400 calls for help were made, with fallen trees crushing cars, bringing down powerlines and damaging homes.  A driver trapped under a tree in Croydon Park was freed after an hour, as SES volunteers worked through the night.  Flights at Sydney Airport were briefly disrupted, but operations have returned to normal today as repairs continue. title: Emergency Food Aid Arrives In Jamaica For Hurricane Melissa Victims | 10 News
description: Boxes containing vital food supplies of rice, lentils, canned fish and meat have arrived in the Caribbean following the devastation of Hurricane Melissa.  The category five hurricane made landfall in Jamaica, the strongest of which the country has ever seen.  At least 28 people have been killed in Jamaica as a result of the hurricane, with the World Food Programme predicting at least five million people are in need of aid. title: Rome’s Medieval Tower Collapses During Repairs, One Worker Critically Injured | 10 News
description: A medieval tower undergoing renovations in central Rome has partially collapsed, critically injuring one worker and trapping another for hours as crowds watched emergency crews carry out a dramatic rescue.  Firefighters were forced to retreat at one point when a second section of the 13th-century Torre dei Conti gave way, sending dust and debris into the air near the Colosseum and Roman Forum.  One worker was freed in critical condition, while three others were rescued unharmed and no bystanders were injured.  Emergency crews are now stabilising the crumbling tower to prevent further collapse.
